 Pictures circulating on WhatsApp, have warned motorists to steer clear of Machadodorp as protests erupted once again. The town was plunged into chaos earlier this week when a video of two men attempting to forcefully arrest another man, surfaced. Motorists are warned to avoid the N4 past Machadodorp. A local businessman lost his shop after it was looted and set alight. The two men, Bruce Botha and Wayne Swart, was arrested and charged with assault with the intent to cause grievous bodily harm. They were released on R500 earlier this morning.  Armed robbery at Auctioneers Pastor gunned down during church service Three killed in shootout with Police Suspects might be linked to seven other robberies • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za